<h2>‚ö†Ô∏è Issues to Address</h2>
<h3>1. <strong>Hardcoded Version String</strong></h3>
<pre><code class="language-python"># cli.py:168
version=&quot;%(prog)s 0.1.0&quot;  # Hardcoded!

# __init__.py:22
__version__ = &quot;0.1.0&quot;  # Also here
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Problem</strong>: Version is duplicated and must be updated in multiple places.</p>
<p><strong>Fix</strong>: Import from <code>__init__.py</code>:</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">from chromdetect import __version__
version=f&quot;%(prog)s {__version__}&quot;
</code></pre>
<hr />
<h3>2. <strong>Missing Exit Codes</strong></h3>
<p>Only uses <code>0</code> (success) and <code>1</code> (error). Best practice is distinct codes:</p>
<table>
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Code</th>
<th>Meaning</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>0</td>
<td>Success</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>General error</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td>CLI usage error (argparse default)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>64</td>
<td>Input file error (EX_NOINPUT)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>65</td>
<td>Data format error (EX_DATAERR)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>74</td>
<td>I/O error (EX_IOERR)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<hr />
<h3>3. <strong>No Verbose Mode</strong></h3>
<p>Has <code>--quiet</code> but no <code>--verbose/-v</code> for debugging. Note: <code>-v</code> is taken by <code>--version</code>.</p>
<p><strong>Suggestion</strong>: Use <code>-V</code> for verbose or <code>--verbose</code> only.</p>
<hr />
<h3>4. <strong>Missing Input Validation</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>No check if input is actually a FASTA file</li>
<li>No file size warning for very large files</li>
<li>No check for empty results</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<h3>5. <strong>Limited Filtering Options</strong></h3>
<p>Only <code>--chromosomes-only</code>. Could add:
- <code>--unplaced-only</code>
- <code>--min-confidence FLOAT</code>
